Repo-ready anti-leak rules

I’d put this in ABSTRACTION_BOUNDARIES.md:

Abstraction hygiene rules
	1.	Names are not powers. A symbolic label does not imply agency or truth.
	2.	No upward smuggling. Lower layers cannot depend on metaphorical layers.
	3.	No silent promotion. Repetition does not create invariants.
	4.	Narrative is not evidence. Symbolic coherence is never proof.
	5.	All transforms leave tracks. Preserve provenance and confidence.
	6.	Roles compile to constraints. Personas are interface skins over configs.
	7.	Daemons are functions, not selves.
	8.	Predictions require uncertainty.
	9.	Memory stores status, not ontology.
	10.	Every elegant abstraction must survive ugly test cases.

